+/*
+ * pouch syscall-number table - musl's aarch64 table retargeted to the
+ * Thylacine syscall ABI (kernel/include/thylacine/syscall.h).
+ *
+ * This is the SEAM (POUCH-DESIGN.md section 5). Each macro carries either:
+ *   - a Thylacine syscall number, for a call that maps 1:1 onto a native
+ *     Thylacine syscall. Eight such calls at this sub-chunk: read, write,
+ *     close, exit, exit_group, mlockall, getrandom, set_tid_address.
+ *     musl's wrapper issues `svc 0` and the kernel honours it directly.
+ *   - 0xFFFF, the pouch unimplemented-syscall sentinel, for a call with no
+ *     Thylacine equivalent. arch/aarch64/syscall_arch.h short-circuits the
+ *     sentinel to -ENOSYS WITHOUT issuing a trap: an un-retargeted POSIX
+ *     call is a clean ENOSYS (invariant P-3) and no foreign syscall number
+ *     ever reaches the kernel (invariant P-1).
+ *
+ * exit and exit_group both map to SYS_EXITS - whole-process exit at v1.0;
+ * the per-thread exit distinction lands with the pouch-threads sub-chunk.
+ *
+ * Wider POSIX (open, mmap, the socket family) is NOT 1:1 - pouch implements
+ * it in C in its lower half as sequences of Thylacine syscalls; those
+ * macros stay at the sentinel until the owning sub-chunk lands.
+ *
+ * Regenerate after re-vendoring musl with the awk retarget recorded in the
+ * 0001-pouch-syscall-seam.patch header.
+ */
